---
/**
 * Shared content-generation engine diagram for the "What I'm Building" section.
 *
 * Tells the real dependency story from the WeGoFwd2020 shared-library graph:
 * one engine (wegofwd-llm) is proven in Mentible first, then reused across the
 * other products. Solid edge = the dependency is wired in code today; dashed =
 * planned. This is why Pramana reads "in build" rather than deployed — the
 * engine it leans on is still being matured in Mentible.
 *
 * Same conventions as LearningDiagram.astro: the SVG is inlined so dark-mode
 * rules key off the site's `.dark` class (not the OS), and every selector is
 * nested under `.engine-diagram` so the SVG's bare selectors can't repaint the
 * rest of the page. Astro also scopes the block automatically.
 */
---

<figure class="engine-diagram">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 680 400" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <title>One shared content-generation engine, proven in Mentible, then reused across the products</title>
    <desc>
      A single shared library, wegofwd-llm, is the content-generation engine. It is proven first in Mentible, which is
      live in production. The same engine is wired into Pramana, which is in build, and is planned for Kathai Chithiram,
      also in build. Solid arrows mark dependencies wired in code today; the dashed arrow marks a planned one.
    </desc>

    {/* Engine */}
    <rect class="engine-b" x="230" y="40" width="220" height="58" rx="8"></rect>
    <text class="node teal-t" x="340" y="64" text-anchor="middle">wegofwd-llm</text>
    <text class="teal-t sub" x="340" y="82" text-anchor="middle">shared content-generation engine</text>

    {/* Edges: engine → products */}
    {/* to Mentible (solid) */}
    <line class="ln" x1="300" y1="98" x2="150" y2="214"></line>
    <polygon class="ah" points="147,218 150,209 156,214"></polygon>
    {/* to Pramana (solid) */}
    <line class="ln" x1="340" y1="98" x2="340" y2="214"></line>
    <polygon class="ah" points="340,218 336,210 344,210"></polygon>
    {/* to Kathai Chithiram (planned, dashed) */}
    <line class="ln dashed" x1="380" y1="98" x2="530" y2="214"></line>
    <polygon class="ah-muted" points="533,218 524,214 530,209"></polygon>
    <text class="muted" x="470" y="150" text-anchor="middle">planned</text>

    {/* Products */}
    {/* Mentible */}
    <rect class="prod-b" x="40" y="218" width="200" height="52" rx="8"></rect>
    <text class="node prod-t" x="140" y="242" text-anchor="middle">Mentible</text>
    <rect class="chip-live" x="78" y="250" width="124" height="20" rx="10"></rect>
    <text class="chip-live-t" x="140" y="264" text-anchor="middle">live · engine proven here</text>

    {/* Pramana */}
    <rect class="prod-b" x="250" y="218" width="180" height="52" rx="8"></rect>
    <text class="node prod-t" x="340" y="242" text-anchor="middle">Pramana</text>
    <rect class="chip-build" x="300" y="250" width="80" height="20" rx="10"></rect>
    <text class="chip-build-t" x="340" y="264" text-anchor="middle">in build</text>

    {/* Kathai Chithiram */}
    <rect class="prod-b" x="440" y="218" width="200" height="52" rx="8"></rect>
    <text class="node prod-t" x="540" y="242" text-anchor="middle">Kathai Chithiram</text>
    <rect class="chip-build" x="500" y="250" width="80" height="20" rx="10"></rect>
    <text class="chip-build-t" x="540" y="264" text-anchor="middle">in build</text>

    {/* Caption + legend */}
    <text class="caption" x="340" y="318" text-anchor="middle"
      >One engine, proven in Mentible first, then reused across the products.</text
    >

    <line class="ln" x1="196" y1="352" x2="236" y2="352"></line>
    <text x="244" y="356">wired in code today</text>
    <line class="ln dashed" x1="404" y1="352" x2="444" y2="352"></line>
    <text x="452" y="356">planned</text>
  </svg>
</figure>

<style>
  .engine-diagram {
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0;
  }

  .engine-diagram svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    font-family: var(--aw-font-heading), ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  /* Every selector nested under .engine-diagram — the SVG's own bare selectors
     would otherwise repaint the whole document. */
  .engine-diagram text {
    font-size: 12px;
    fill: #475569;
  }
  .engine-diagram .node {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .engine-diagram .sub {
    font-size: 11px;
  }
  .engine-diagram .caption {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    font-style: italic;
    fill: #475569;
  }
  .engine-diagram .muted {
    font-size: 11px;
    fill: #94a3b8;
  }
  .engine-diagram .teal-t {
    fill: #115e59;
  }
  .engine-diagram .prod-t {
    fill: #334155;
  }
  .engine-diagram .engine-b {
    fill: #ccfbf1;
    stroke: #5eead4;
  }
  .engine-diagram .prod-b {
    fill: #f8fafc;
    stroke: #e2e8f0;
  }
  .engine-diagram .ln {
    stroke: #64748b;
    stroke-width: 1.25;
    fill: none;
  }
  .engine-diagram .ln.dashed {
    stroke-dasharray: 5 4;
    stroke: #94a3b8;
  }
  .engine-diagram .ah {
    fill: #64748b;
  }
  .engine-diagram .ah-muted {
    fill: #94a3b8;
  }
  .engine-diagram .chip-live {
    fill: #d1fae5;
    stroke: #6ee7b7;
  }
  .engine-diagram .chip-live-t {
    font-size: 11px;
    fill: #065f46;
  }
  .engine-diagram .chip-build {
    fill: #fef3c7;
    stroke: #fcd34d;
  }
  .engine-diagram .chip-build-t {
    font-size: 11px;
    fill: #92400e;
  }

  /* Keyed to the site's `.dark` class (tailwind darkMode: 'class'), not the OS. */
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram text {
    fill: #cbd5e1;
  }
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .caption {
    fill: #94a3b8;
  }
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .muted {
    fill: #64748b;
  }
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .prod-t {
    fill: #e2e8f0;
  }
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .prod-b {
    fill: rgb(148 163 184 / 7%);
    stroke: #334155;
  }
  /* Chips keep their light fills in dark mode, so their dark ink must persist —
     the bare `html.dark ... text` rule above would otherwise wash them out. */
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .teal-t {
    fill: #115e59;
  }
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .chip-live-t {
    fill: #065f46;
  }
  :global(html.dark) .engine-diagram .chip-build-t {
    fill: #92400e;
  }
</style>
